name: The mix media artist
description:
These brushes are made to blend analog and digital drawing together
and they are great for adding details to your analog drawings.

These brushes is also made to give a good performance without needing a Cintiq, I can really recommend to use them with a intuos4 and 5.

I have also included some good basic brushes that has no texture but a great brush tip and sensitive settings so you can sketch out your work before cleaning it on paper for example.

I have enhanced all the pencils with color dynamics to give extra depth in the tones. 

The color pencils are set to match actual scans drawn with col-erase pencils. 

This package only works in Photoshop cs5 or cs6. 

What do you get?

5 Basic line brushes.
(All of them have pre installed colors and color dynamic settings)

4 Different toned mechanical pencils
(All of them have pre installed colors and color dynamic settings)

3 Different toned mechanical pencils shaders 
(All of them have pre installed colors and color dynamic settings)

2 Blue pencils (matched to scanned artwork)
(All of them have pre installed colors and color dynamic settings)

2 Indigo blue pencils (matched to scanned artwork)
(All of them have pre installed colors and color dynamic settings)

2 Light blue pencils (matched to scanned artwork)
(All of them have pre installed colors and color dynamic settings)

2 Scarlet red pencils (matched to scanned artwork)
(All of them have pre installed colors and color dynamic settings)

2 Vermillion red pencils (matched to scanned artwork)
(All of them have pre installed colors and color dynamic settings)

2 Tuscan red pencils (matched to scanned artwork)
(All of them have pre installed colors and color dynamic settings)

2 Basic marker brushes (new cs 5 brush system) 

7 Different erasers (ranging from very soft to very sharp)


How to change the color settings for the color dynamic brushes?

If you wish adjust or make other colors for the color dynamic brushes you just have to change the foreground and background color and the save the tool preset again with the option box checked on ¨include color¨. 

For optimal performance and depth in relation to the pressure sensitivity you should always make the foreground color darker than the background color.

name: The illustrator advanced
description:
The brushes are imitating the traditional pencil, pencil shaders  from 9B to 9H and graphite powder
It is even closer to the real thing than the previous illustrator package and it is better for softer looking pencil drawings.

What do you get?

1 Graphite powder brush.

1 Paper dirt brush

2 Different broad pencil shaders

4 Different textured drawing pencils (HB,2B,4B and 6B)

9 Different stroke shaders from 9B to 9H with all the right grey tones as a real life pencil and all in 3 different sizes per pencil. 

4 Different erasers (they variates from soft to hard and precise)

1 Tonal value eraser ( you tap on the area and it takes one tone of)

More or less all brushes are preprogrammed with a grey value to get the best look of pencil and several of them, even though there are the same are preprogrammed in different sizes for faster use.

name: The illustrator advanced 2
description:
The brushes are imitating the traditional pencil, pencil shaders  from 9B to 9H and graphite powder in a very rough textured way.
Both sets are tested and work great in color as well, I will recommend that you use pantone colors since the pencil makes the color transparent and mixed by default of the shading process.
It is now more easy to make a real full shaded drawing without all the real pencil problems and it gives you the freedom to play with all good possibility's that also comes with photoshop.

An extra thing to this set is that you'll get to version of the brushes.
The first version is a normal subtile texture and version 2 gives you a set that has a more present texture just like if you changed to a more rough paper.

What do you get?

1 Charcoal pencil

1 Graphite powder brush.

2 Different sketch pencils (4B and 9B)

4 Different drawing pencils (H,HB,2B, and 4B)

4 Different drawing shaders (H,HB,2B, and 4B)

9 Different pencil stroke shaders (9H to 9B)

9 Different broad pencil shaders (9H to 9B)

4 Different erasers (they variates from soft to hard and precise)

1 Tonal value eraser ( you tap on the area and it takes one tone of)

More or less all brushes are preprogrammed with a grey value to get the best look of pencil and several of them, even though there are the same are preprogrammed in different sizes for faster use.

Additional illustration made by my friend David Pellet 
http://depe-bd.blogspot.com/

name: The paint artist
description:
These brushes are made to target the realistic feel of wet paint, mechanical pencil and colored pencils (like col-erase).

The brushes are a mix of the new generation paint brushes introduced in Photoshop cs 5 and the traditional Photoshop brush system for the pencils that I have enhanced with color dynamics to give extra depth in the tones. 

I have also included some mixer brushes that helps you get the most realistic and easy mix of colors direct on canvas.

This package only works in Photoshop cs 5 or higher.

What do you get?

6 wet paint brushes (with a touch of paper texture)

1 basic filler brush (to make masks or fill shapes before starting to paint)

4 Different toned mechanical pencils
(All of them have pre installed colors and color dynamic settings)

3 Different toned mechanical pencils shaders 
(All of them have pre installed colors and color dynamic settings)

3 Blue pencils (1 blue pencil, 1 blue pencil soft and 1 blue pencil shader. All of them have pre installed colors and color dynamic settings)

3 Red pencils (1 red pencil, 1 red pencil soft and 1 red pencil shader. All of them have pre installed colors and color dynamic settings)

7 Different erasers (ranging from very soft to very sharp)

2 mixer brushes.

How to change the color settings for the color dynamic brushes?

If you wish adjust or make other colors for the color dynamic brushes you just have to change the foreground and background color and the save the tool preset again with the option box checked on ¨include color¨. 

For optimal performance and depth in relation to the pressure sensitivity you should always make the foreground color darker than the background color.

name: The watercolor artist
description:
The brushes are imitating traditional watercolor wash and watercolor pen. I have configured all these brushes from the wonderful new standard watercolor brushes you get in the new Photoshop CS6.

When in use I highly recommend to use the option to angle the pen for optimal watercolor edge effect.

The brushes only work in Photoshop CS6 due to the new brush system.

What do you get?

8 Different calibrated watercolor brushes.

1 Watercolor pen

1 Salt brush

1 Texture brush

4 Different erasers
